title: Jamshlu
content:
40°41′26″N 44°16′25″E﻿ / ﻿40.69056°N 44.27361°E﻿ / 40.69056; 44.27361

Jamshlu or Jamushvan (Armenian: Ջամշլու or Ջամուշվան; Kurdish: Camuşlû) is a village in the Alagyaz Municipality of the Aragatsotn Province of Armenia. The town is mostly populated by Kurds.[2]
